        refine' eventually_nhdsWithin_iff.mpr _
        filter_upwards [Ioo_mem_nhds (show t > t0 - h by linarith) (show t < t0 + h * (âŒŠ(t - t0) / hâŒ‹â‚Š + 1) by nlinarith [Nat.lt_floor_add_one ((t - t0) / h), mul_div_cancelâ‚€ (t - t0) h_pos.ne'])] with x hx hx'; simp_all +decide [mul_comm h];
        rw [eulerPath];
        rw [floor_eq_of_mem_Ico h_pos t0 âŒŠ(t - t0) / hâŒ‹â‚Š x âŸ¨by nlinarith [Nat.floor_le (show 0 â‰¤ (t - t0) / h from div_nonneg (by linarith) h_pos.le), mul_div_cancelâ‚€ (t - t0) h_pos.ne'], by nlinarith [mul_div_cancelâ‚€ (x - t0) h_pos.ne']âŸ©];
      rw [Filter.EventuallyEq.hasDerivWithinAt_iff] at *
      any_goals tauto
      rw [hasDerivWithinAt_iff_tendsto]; simp +decide [â† sub_smul, eulerDeriv]
    exact hasDerivWithinAt_Ioi_iff_Ici.mp (h_right_deriv t ht)

/-
On the interval [t_n, t_{n+1}), the Euler path is given by the affine function starting at y_n with slope v(t_n, y_n).
